  "prompt": "How can I block Skype on Mac?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to block Skype on a Mac:\n\n1. Uninstall Skype\n- Open Finder\n- Go to Applications\n- Drag Skype to the Trash\n- Empty the Trash\n\n2. Parental Controls\n- Open System Preferences\n- Click \"Parental Controls\"\n- Select the user account\n- Go to \"Apps\" tab\n- Check the box to block Skype\n\n3. Firewall Settings\n- Open System Preferences\n- Click \"Security & Privacy\"\n- Go to \"Firewall\" tab\n- Click \"Firewall Options\"\n- Add Skype to blocked applications\n\n4. Third-Party Blocking Software\n- Use apps like \"Cold Turkey\" or \"Freedom\"\n- These can block Skype and other applications\n\n5. DNS Blocking\n- Modify your Mac's hosts file to block Skype's servers\n- Requires technical knowledge\n\n6. Router-Level Blocking\n- Log into your router settings\n- Block Skype's IP addresses or domain\n\n7. Delete Skype Startup Item\n- Go to System Preferences\n- Select \"Users & Groups\"\n- Click \"Login Items\"\n- Remove Skype from startup list\n\nChoose the method that best suits your specific needs and technical comfort level.",
